title: Grand Exchange/Non-tradeable items

properties.name: description
properties.value: Non-tradeable items, in terms of the Grand Exchange, are items that are tradeable, but not on the Grand Exchange. These items must therefore be exchanged via the standard trading interface.

content:
Non-tradeable items, in terms of the Grand Exchange, are items that are tradeable, but not on the Grand Exchange. These items must therefore be exchanged via the standard trading interface.

Because of this, it may be difficult to obtain significant quantities of these items. Although most non-tradeable items are quest-related items or otherwise low in value when sold to shops, certain players seek them for collecting purposes. An example of this is players collecting burnt food.

Unique items, especially those no longer able to be obtained by the player themselves, are often more sought-after than non-tradeable items such as various stages of chargeable jewellery.

Contents

  • 1 List of non-tradeable items
    • 1.1 Burnt food
    • 1.2 Fire arrows
    • 1.3 Item packs
    • 1.4 Minigames
    • 1.5 Satchels
    • 1.6 Quest items
    • 1.7 Other

List of non-tradeable items[edit | edit source]

Not directly listed:

  • Baskets partially filled with fruit (Bananas (2), Strawberries (4), etc.).
  • Black masks that have charges, and do not currently have the maximum amount of charges.
  • Partially completed Cooking items (Part summer pie (watermelon), Uncooked pizza, etc.).
  • Partially eaten food (2/3 cake, Half an admiral pie, etc.).
  • Enchanted jewellery that has charges, and does not currently have its maximum amount of charges (with the exception of amulet of glory (4) and amulet of glory (t) (4)).
